open git bash

then specify name and e-mail address by using 
   git config --global user.name "Amith V"
   git config --global user.email amith007v@gmail.com

set the default branch name to "main" for new repositories that are created
  git config --global init.defaultBranch main

then go to the desired file
   cd filename

then initilise the file
   git init

then we check the status
   git status

then we track the files in the folder
   git add file.name
to remove a tracked file
   git rm --cached file.name
git add . = adds all files

then check the status again

then create a .gitignore in the folder

then we commit the files
   git commit -m "message"

then check the status again

if there is a change in a file then
   git diff 
will show us what the difference is
